 Some gunmen who are suspected to be terrorists have reportedly abducted a woman, her baby and two other persons in Zaria, Kaduna State. Available report indicated that “In the early hours of Friday, gunmen attacked the Tudun Mun tsira village of Zangon Shanu, Samaru in Sabon Gari Local Government Area of Kaduna State. “They kidnapped a nursing mother and her baby. An elderly man, Mallam Abubakar Garba Aliyu, and his son, Salim Abubakar, were also taken away. “Abubakar and his family relocated to the area recently. Today, he was kidnapped.” “The gunmen who rode motorbikes were many. “Initially, we thought they were from kasuwar Da’a axis in Giwa Local Government Area which is close to us. “They kidnapped the nursing mother and her baby at Tudun Mun Tsira village before proceeding to Hayin Liman where they kidnapped Alhaji Abubakar and his son.” Reactions had yet to be given by the authorities on the sad development. 